## 7. IMPORTANT PATTERNS FOR THE NEXT LLM

### How Single-Page Apps Work in This Project
The Teacher and Parent dashboards are **JavaScript SPAs** — one HTML file with a `<div id="mainContent">` that gets dynamically replaced by JavaScript functions:

```javascript
// Sidebar click → loadView('chat') → calls loadChat() → replaces mainContent innerHTML
function loadView(view, el) {
    document.querySelectorAll('.menu-item').forEach(e => e.classList.remove('active'));
    if (el) el.classList.add('active');
    const c = document.getElementById('mainContent');
    c.innerHTML = '<div class="loader">Loading...</div>';
    const views = { dashboard: loadDashboard, chat: loadChat, ... };
    (views[view] || loadDashboard)();
}
```

### How Auth Middleware Works
Every route file has its own copy of the auth middleware (not centralized). Example:
```javascript
function teacherAuth(req, res, next) {
    const token = req.headers.authorization.split(' ')[1];
    const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET || 'super_admin_secret_key_2024');
    if (decoded.type !== 'teacher') return res.status(401).json({...});
    req.teacherId = decoded.teacherId;
    req.schoolId = decoded.schoolId;
    next();
}
```

### How Chat Teacher Resolution Works (3-step fallback)
In `routes/chat.js` (parent side), finding the teacher to chat with:
1. `student.teacherId` → direct reference
2. `Teacher.findOne({ isClassTeacher: true, classTeacherFor.className: student.className })`
3. `Teacher.findOne({ classAssignments: { $elemMatch: { className, section } } })`

### CSS Pattern
All pages use **inline `<style>` blocks** in the HTML `<head>`. No external CSS framework. Design tokens:
- Primary: `#4338CA` (indigo)
